public interface SerializableMessage
Represents a serializable message or a piece of a serializable message.

Concrete classes that implement this interface that also wish to be deserializable should also support the reverse operation by creating a constructor that takes a single (little-endian) ByteBuffer as its only argument.

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    void addToBuffer​(java.nio.ByteBuffer buffer)
    Writes this message into the given buffer as a contiguous range of bytes.

  • Method Details

    • addToBuffer

      void addToBuffer​(java.nio.ByteBuffer buffer)
      Writes this message into the given buffer as a contiguous range of bytes. This is so that a message can be sent. Implementors may assume that the buffer has been configured to be little-endian and that its position is at the point where they should begin writing. Once it has finished, the position should be immediately after the last byte written by this method.
      Parameters:
      buffer - The buffer to write into.
